goals.question: What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?
goals.rationale: A box plot can show the median, quartiles, and outliers of the yield distribution, giving an idea of the central tendency and spread of the data.

goals.question: How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?
goals.visualization: violin plot of yield by variety
goals.rationale: A violin plot can show the distribution of yield for each variety, allowing for comparison of the central tendency and spread of the data across different categories.

goals.question: What is the yield trend over time for each site?
goals.visualization: line plot of yield by year, grouped by site
goals.rationale: A line plot can show the trend of yield over time for each site, allowing for comparison of the performance of each site and potential factors affecting yield.

goals.question: What is the distribution of yield for each site?
goals.visualization: histogram of yield, grouped by site
goals.rationale: A histogram can show the distribution of yield for each site, allowing for comparison of the central tendency and spread of the data across different locations.

goals.question: Is there a correlation between yield and year?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of yield by year
goals.rationale: A scatter plot can show the relationship between yield and year, allowing for analysis of potential trends or patterns in the data.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    plt.boxplot(data['yield'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('What is the average yield of barley across all sites and years?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = plt.subplot(111)
    ax.violinplot(dataset=[data[data['variety'] == variety]['yield'] for variety in data['variety'].unique()], showmeans=True)
    ax.set_xticks(range(1, len(data['variety'].unique()) + 1))
    ax.set_xticklabels(data['variety'].unique(), rotation=45, ha='right')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.title('How does the yield vary across different barley varieties?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['year'] = pd.to_datetime(data['year'], format='%Y', errors='ignore')
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    for site in data['site'].unique():
        site_data = data[data['site'] == site]
        plt.plot(site_data['year'], site_data['yield'], label=site)
    plt.title('What is the yield trend over time for each site?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Year')
    plt.ylabel('Yield (bushels per acre)')
    plt.legend()
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['yield'] = pd.to_numeric(data['yield'], errors='coerce')
    data = data.dropna(subset=['yield'])
    data['site'] = data['site'].astype('category')
    sites = data['site'].unique()
    for site in sites:
        plt.hist(data[data['site'] == site]['yield'], alpha=0.5, label=site)
    plt.legend(loc='upper right')
    plt.xlabel('Yield')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of yield for each site?', wrap=True)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
